      "source": [
        "# ===============================\n",
        "# Mall Customer Analysis\n",
        "# EDA + Hypothesis Testing\n",
        "# ===============================\n",
        "\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import seaborn as sns\n",
        "from scipy import stats\n",
        "\n",
        "sns.set(style=\"whitegrid\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# ===============================\n",
        "# Load dataset\n",
        "# ===============================\n",
        "df = pd.read_csv('/content/Mall_Customers.csv')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Rename column for easy use\n",
        "df.rename(columns={'Annual Income (k$)': 'Annual_Income_K$'}, inplace=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(df.head())\n",
        "print(df.info())\n",
        "print(df.describe())\n",
        "print(df.isnull().sum())\n",
        "\n",
        "# ===============================\n",
        "# EDA & Visualizations\n",
        "# ===============================\n",
        "\n",
        "# Gender distribution\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(5,4))\n",
        "df['Genre'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar')\n",
        "plt.title('Gender Distribution')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Gender')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Count')\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.savefig('gender_distribution.png')\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Age distribution\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))\n",
        "plt.hist(df['Age'], bins=20)\n",
        "plt.title('Age Distribution')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Age')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Count')\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.savefig('age_distribution.png')\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Income distribution\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))\n",
        "plt.hist(df['Annual_Income_K$'], bins=15)\n",
        "plt.title('Annual Income Distribution')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Income (K$)')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Count')\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.savefig('income_distribution.png')\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Age vs Spending\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))\n",
        "plt.scatter(df['Age'], df['Spending Score (1-100)'])\n",
        "plt.title('Age vs Spending Score')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Age')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Spending Score')\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.savefig('age_vs_spending.png')\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Income vs Spending\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))\n",
        "plt.scatter(df['Annual_Income_K$'], df['Spending Score (1-100)'])\n",
        "plt.title('Income vs Spending Score')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Annual Income (K$)')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Spending Score')\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.savefig('income_vs_spending.png')\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Correlation heatmap\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))\n",
        "sns.heatmap(df.corr(numeric_only=True), annot=True, cmap='coolwarm')\n",
        "plt.title('Correlation Heatmap')\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.savefig('heatmap.png')\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# ===============================\n",
        "# Hypothesis Testing\n",
        "# ===============================\n",
        "\n",
        "# T-test: Gender vs Spending\n",
        "male = df[df['Genre'] == 'Male']['Spending Score (1-100)']\n",
        "female = df[df['Genre'] == 'Female']['Spending Score (1-100)']\n",
        "t_stat, p_val = stats.ttest_ind(male, female)\n",
        "print(\"T-test (Gender vs Spending): t =\", t_stat, \", p =\", p_val)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Pearson correlation: Age vs Spending\n",
        "r, p_corr = stats.pearsonr(df['Age'], df['Spending Score (1-100)'])\n",
        "print(\"Pearson Correlation (Age vs Spending): r =\", r, \", p =\", p_corr)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Chi-square: Gender vs Spending Category\n",
        "df['Spending_category'] = pd.cut(\n",
        "    df['Spending Score (1-100)'],\n",
        "    bins=[0, 40, 80, 100],\n",
        "    labels=['Low', 'Medium', 'High']\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "table = pd.crosstab(df['Genre'], df['Spending_category'])\n",
        "chi2, p_chi, dof, exp = stats.chi2_contingency(table)\n",
        "print(\"Chi-square Test: chi2 =\", chi2, \", p =\", p_chi)\n",
        "\n",
        "# ANOVA: Spending across Age groups\n",
        "young = df[df['Age'] <= 30]['Spending Score (1-100)']\n",
        "middle = df[(df['Age'] > 30) & (df['Age'] <= 50)]['Spending Score (1-100)']\n",
        "old = df[df['Age'] > 50]['Spending Score (1-100)']\n",
        "\n",
        "f_stat, p_anova = stats.f_oneway(young, middle, old)\n",
        "print(\"ANOVA Test: F =\", f_stat, \", p =\", p_anova)"
      ],
